The paper deals with optimization problems related to routing vehicles to serve requests in a metric space, which is a classic problem in computer science. The focus is on point-to-point requests with release-time constraints, which are common in online ride and delivery services. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity), which are all relevant to the problem of optimizing routing in online services.
